description:
Dear Divers! 

Welcome to 2022, hopefully, a year of better activities for the club. It is time to assemble and elect the Committee for this year.

We are going to proceed with renewing the committee similar to last year due to the Covid-19 limitation during wintertime. This might give a fresh start to both the new year and the school year and we are sure we will have an amazing year of diving. 

**Location: Melbourne University Dive Shed**
**Time: 8 February 2022, 7:00 pm**

*We will also have a sausage sizzle!*

**Nominations**
It is the ordinary business of AGM to nominate new committee members: 
Nominations must be delivered to the Secretary (Burak) no less than 7 days before the date fixed for the holding of the annual general meeting;
Made in writing, signed by two members of the Club and accompanied by the written consent of the candidate (which may be endorsed on the form of nomination). 
A candidate may only be nominated for one office, or as an ordinary member of the committee, prior to the annual general meeting.
If insufficient nominations are received to fill all vacancies on the committee, the candidates nominated shall be deemed to be elected and further nominations may be received at the annual general meeting.
If the number of nominations received is equal to the number of vacancies to be filled, the persons nominated shall be deemed to be elected.
If the number of nominations exceeds the number of vacancies to be filled, a ballot must be held.

**Committee Roles**
( a) President;
( b) a Vice-President/Safety Officer;
( c) a Treasurer;
( d) a Secretary/Public Officer;
( e) a Gear Officer;
( f) a Dive Coordinator;
( g) a Course Coordinator;
( h) a Social Officer;
( i) a Boat Officer; 
( j) an Ordinary Member (club car); and
( k) an Ordinary Member (webmaster).

**AGM Agenda** 
( a) to confirm the minutes of the previous annual general meeting and of any general meeting held since that meeting; and
( b) to receive from the committee reports upon the transactions of the Club during the last preceding financial year; and
( c) to elect officers of the Club and the ordinary member of the committee;

Burak Uslu
secretary@muuc.org.au
burak.uslu@gmail.com

Dear Divers! 

Welcome to 2023. We had  a spectacular year. We are the second most active club in Melbourn University Sports and let's make that the first. 

It is time to assemble and elect the Committee for this year. This is where you - our community, vote for the new members of the committee, as well as nominate and can be nominated for open positions. This is also a great occasion to socialise and discuss any pressing matters for the club. In the finale, the current committee will give you a rundown of our progress so far!

We are going to proceed with renewing the committee similar to last year due to the Covid-19 limitation during wintertime. This might give a fresh start to both the new year and the school year and we are sure we will have an amazing year of diving. 

**Location: Melbourne University Dive Shed**
**Time: 23 March 2022, 6:00 pm**


**Nominations**
It is the ordinary business of AGM to nominate new committee members: 
Nominations must be delivered to the Secretary (Burak) no less than 7 days before the date fixed for the holding of the annual general meeting;
Made in writing, signed by two members of the Club and accompanied by the written consent of the candidate (which may be endorsed on the form of nomination). 
A candidate may only be nominated for one office, or as an ordinary member of the committee, prior to the annual general meeting.
If insufficient nominations are received to fill all vacancies on the committee, the candidates nominated shall be deemed to be elected and further nominations may be received at the annual general meeting.
If the number of nominations received is equal to the number of vacancies to be filled, the persons nominated shall be deemed to be elected.
If the number of nominations exceeds the number of vacancies to be filled, a ballot must be held.

**Committee Roles**
( a) President;
( b) a Vice-President/Safety Officer;
( c) a Treasurer;
( d) a Secretary/Public Officer;
( e) a Gear Officer;
( f) a Dive Coordinator;
( g) a Course Coordinator;
( h) a Social Officer;
( i) a Boat Officer; 
( j) an Ordinary Member (club car); and
( k) an Ordinary Member (webmaster).

**AGM Agenda** 
( a) to confirm the minutes of the previous annual and special general meeting and of any general meeting held since that meeting; and
( b) to receive from the committee reports upon the transactions of the Club during the last preceding financial year; and
( c) to elect officers of the Club and the ordinary member of the committee;


**Brief Description**
( a)  *President*: President represents the club inside Melbourne University and outside. Coordinates committee meetings, club efforts and external communications. President oversees all club activities and liaises with Melbourne University Sports. ;
( b)  *Vice-President/Safety Officer*: fills in for President in their absence and assures a safe club environment;
( c)  *Treasurer*: Club's accountant and making sure the club stays sustainable. Provides monthly cash flow updates and reports this to Melbourne University and Victorian Public Affairs.;
( d)  *Secretary/Public Officer*: keep all paperwork up to date, all external communications and paperwork are intact with  Victorian Public affairs and Melbourne University ;
( e)  *Gear Officer*: Maintain and look after all scuba equipment, and schedules and assures all gears, tanks, and compressors are regularly maintained.;
( f) *Dive Coordinator*: help coordinate weekly diving trips, help divers with an extent of local diving knowledge;
( g)  *Course Coordinator*: Work with instructors and students and organise scuba courses.;
( h)  *Social Officer*: Organise social events: BBQ, and movie nights, as well as help with social media communications;
( i)  *Boat Officer*: Look after and maintain our lovely Blue Devil;
( j)  *Ordinary Member* (club car): help all club activities, and trips as well as maintaining our car; and
( k)  *Ordinary Member* (webmaster): help with all club activities, and trips as well as help with social media communications.


Burak Uslu
secretary@muuc.org.au
burak.uslu@gmail.com

